cs.LG, cs.CV, cs.AI, cs.NE, cs.GR 

This paper focuses on Generative Adversarial Networks (GANs) and their architectures for reducing mode collapse. The most relevant sub-category is likely cs.LG (Machine Learning), as GANs are a popular topic in this field. Additionally, the paper uses MNIST digits as input data, which falls under the sub-category cs.CV (Computer Vision). The paper also discusses the mathematical theory behind the models, which could place it in the sub-category cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). The use of objective functions and penalty terms may also suggest the sub-categories cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) and cs.GR (Graphics).
